The '''French Wikipedia''' ({{lang-{{#property:P424}}|{{#property:P1448}}}}) is the [[French-language]] edition of the free [[online encyclopedia]] [[Wikipedia]]. This edition was started in March 2001, and has [[:fr:Special:Statistics|{{NUMBEROF|ARTICLES|fr|N}}]] [[encyclopedia article|articles]] as of {{Currentmonthday}}, {{CURRENTYEAR}}, making it the fifth-largest Wikipedia overall, after the [[English Wikipedia|English]]-, [[Dutch Wikipedia|Dutch]]-, [[German Wikipedia|German]]-, [[Swedish Wikipedia|Swedish]]- and [[Cebuano Wikipedia|Cebuano]]-language editions, the largest Wikipedia edition in a [[Romance language]]. It has the third-largest number of edits. It was also the third edition, after the English Wikipedia and German Wikipedia, to exceed 1 million [[encyclopedia]] articles: this occurred on 23 September 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.zdnet.fr/actualites/wikipedia-en-francais-depasse-le-million-d-articles-39754828.htm|title=Wikipédia en français dépasse le million d'articles|work=ZDNet France}}</ref> In April 2016, the project had 4657 active editors who made at least five edits in that month.

In 2008, the French encyclopaedia, ''[[Quid (encyclopedia)|Quid]]'', cancelled its 2008 edition, citing falling sales on competition from the French edition of Wikipedia.<ref>Litchfield, John. "[https://www.independent.co.uk/news/europe/frances-favourite-encyclopaedia-falls-victim-to-wikipedia-784420.html France's favourite encyclopaedia falls victim to Wikipedia]." ''[[The Independent]]''. Wednesday 20 February 2008. Retrieved on 26 June 2013.</ref>

{{as of|2014|June}}, Wikipedia has an [[Alexa Internet|Alexa]] ranking of 6 and 5.06% of those visits are to the French-language edition.<ref name="alexa">{{cite web|url=http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/wikipedia.org|title=Wikipedia.org Site Info|publisher=[[Alexa Internet]]|accessdate=2014-04-01}}</ref> As of {{CURRENTMONTHNAME}} {{CURRENTYEAR}}, there are {{formatnum:{{#expr:{{NUMBEROF|USERS|fr}}round -3}}}} users, {{NUMBEROF|ADMINS|fr}} admins and {{formatnum:{{NUMBEROF|FILES|fr}}}} files on the French Wikipedia.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://stats.wikimedia.org/EN/TablesWikipediaFR.htm|title=Wikipedia Statistics - Tables - French|work=wikimedia.org}}</ref>

On 2 December 2014, the French-language Wikipedia encyclopedia became the 3rd<ref>{{cite web|url=https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/List_of_Wikipedias_by_edits_per_article|title=List of Wikipedias by edits per article|work=wikimedia.org}}</ref> linguistic edition by number of registered users since its creation, overtaking for the first time the German edition, with {{formatnum:2022504}} registered users,<ref>[[:fr:Spécial:Statistiques]]</ref><ref>[[:de:Spezial:Statistik]]</ref> behind the English ({{formatnum:23300456}})<ref>[[Special:Statistics]]</ref> and Spanish ({{formatnum:3401493}})<ref>{{cite web|url=https://es.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Especial:Estad%C3%ADsticas&action=raw|title=Estadísticas|work=es.wikipedia.org}}</ref> language editions.

According to a 2013 study by the [[Oxford Internet Institute]], [[Ségolène Royal]] ([[:fr:Ségolène Royal|FR]]) and [[unidentified flying object]] ([[:fr:objet volant non identifié|objet volant non identifié]]) were the most controversial articles on the French Wikipedia.<ref>{{cite web|author1=Taha Yasseri |author2=Anselm Spoerri |author3=Mark Graham |author4=János Kertész |title=The most controversial topics in Wikipedia: A multilingual and geographical analysis|date=8 Jul 2013|arxiv=1305.5566v2}}</ref>

