[[File:PairofCandlesticks-BoultonFothergill-BMA.jpg|thumb|Pair of silver candlesticks made by [[Matthew Boulton]] and [[John Fothergill, Birmingham|John Fothergill]] in Birmingham, England, 1773 or 1774.]]
A '''largeworker''' was a form of [[silversmith]] in England from the 17th to the early 20th centuries who made items of a larger size such as dishes or candlesticks.<ref>[http://www.millersantiquesguide.com/a-to-z/largeworker/ Largeworker.] Miller's Antiques and Collectables. Retrieved 8 December 2017.</ref> When craftsmen registered their mark they would classify themselves as "goldworker", "smallworker", or "largeworker" according to their skill and specialism.<ref>[http://www.thesilversociety.org/smallwork.php Smallwork.] The Silver Society. Retrieved 8 December 2017.</ref>

