{{Infobox language |name=Nagumi |nativename=Ngong |region=[[Cameroon]] |extinct=ca. 2000 |ref=e19 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]]? ([[Bantu Zone A|Zone A]]) |fam6=[[Mbam languages|Mbam]] |fam7=[[Jarawan languages|Jarawan]] |iso3=ngv |glotto=nagu1244 |glottorefname=Nagumi }}
'''Nagumi''', also known as '''Ngong''' (Gong), is an extinct [[Jarawan languages|Jarawan]] language of the [[North Province (Cameroon)|North Province]] of [[Cameroon]]. It had only two fluent speakers in 1983 and only one in 1995.
